snippet.textDisplay:
Hello my name is Mary Bower, I’m from Northern Ireland and have suffered from quite a few mental illnesses from as long as I remember, I’m 27 years old and am currently in a specialised eating disorder unit miles from home in Scotland. I haven’t spent a Christmas at home for around seven years now and am preparing to spend the holidays once again far from family and home. Christmas time can be a really hard time for so many and my passion is to raise awareness of mental illnesses and how Christmas time can actually be one of the hardest times.

I’ve created a YouTube video trying to convey this and also to show that anyone, at any age, gender or ethnicity etc can suffer from mental illness. I would love if you could share this video, to make people think and perhaps be able to make this time of year a little easier for those suffering.


The link to the video is on my bio, it’s on my YouTube (Mary bower) or Facebook (Mary bower)

I would love for you to share this or even take five minutes to watch it yourself.


https://youtu.be/MaGJD7hIlEg

Thank you for your time! And want you to know...I think you’re brilliant!

Much love

Mary Hannah Bower 💓
